The paper deals with sparse signal reconstruction using probabilistic methods and underdetermined linear models. This suggests that it could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Signal Processing (cs.SP), or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of tomographic projections and compressive samples, which are common in Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-categories. Therefore, these five sub-categories are the most likely candidates for this paper.
